quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  6,28,"Nay! Now is shown clearly to them what they did hide before; and were they to be sent back, they would return to that which they were forbidden, for they are liars"
  6,29,"They say \"There is naught but this life of ours in the world and we shall not be raised again"
  6,30,"But could you see when they are set before their Lord, He says, \"Is not this the real?\" They will say, \"Yea, by our Lord!\" He will say, \"Then taste the penalty because you did disbelieve"
  6,31,"Losers, indeed, are they who disbelieved in meeting Allah, until, when the hour comes suddenly upon them, they say, \"Alas for us, that we were neglectful!\" They shall bear their burdens on their backs; evil is what they bear"
  6,32,"Naught is the life of this world but a game (or pastime) and a sport (or amusement). Surely, better by far is the abode of the Hereafter for those who fear (and do their duty). Will you not understand"
  6,33,"Full well We know that that which they say grieves you; but in truth they deny not you, but the unjust flout the revelations of Allah"
  6,34,"Indeed, Messengers have been called liars before you; but they were patient under denial and persecution until Our help came to them; for there is none to alter the words of Allah. Already has there come to you the story of those He sent in the past"
  6,35,"And if their aversion be hard for you, and if you can, seek for a shaft down into the earth, or a ladder up into the sky, to bring them a sign - if Allah pleased He could have brought them all to guidance - be you not then of the ignorant"